article.description: — Tre Armstrong had a season-high 20 points as California Baptist won its 10th straight home game, easily defeating La Verne 96-41 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Armstrong leads California Baptist over La Verne 96-41
article.linkText: Armstrong leads California Baptist over La Verne 96-41
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. -- — Tre Armstrong had a season-high 20 points as California Baptist won its 10th straight home game, easily defeating La Verne 96-41 on Tuesday night. Reed Nottage had 17 points for California Baptist (10-3). Te'Jon Sawyer added 12 points and 10 rebounds. Juhlawnei Stone had 11 points. The 96 points were a season best for California Baptist, which also achieved a season-high 27 assists. Paul Antonis had 16 points for the Leopards. Brian Adams added 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
